{"source_hash": "18fd555ab6a02698", "candidate": {"id": "cand-029", "name": "Liam O'Sullivan", "raw_cv": "LIAM O'SULLIVAN\nliam.osullivan@email.com | London, UK\n\nDEVOPS ENGINEER\n\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\nDevOps engineer with 4 years of experience in CI/CD, containerisation, and cloud infrastructure. Specialist in GitHub Actions, Docker, and AWS. Background in software development gives me strong empathy for developer workflows. AWS Certified.\n\nEXPERIENCE\n\nDevOps Engineer \u2014 Farewill, London (2022\u2013present)\n- Own CI/CD pipelines for 25+ services (GitHub Actions, Docker, ECS Fargate)\n- Reduced average build time from 18 to 6 minutes through caching and parallelisation\n- Built infrastructure as code for all AWS resources using Terraform; eliminated manual console changes\n- Introduced secrets rotation automation using AWS Secrets Manager + Lambda\n- Security champion: implemented SAST scanning (Semgrep) and dependency auditing in CI\n\nDevOps Engineer \u2014 AND Digital, London (2020\u20132022)\n- Consultant DevOps engineer on projects for retail and logistics clients\n- Delivered Kubernetes migration for a major UK retailer (GKE, Helm, GitLab CI)\n- Built internal Terraform module library used across 8 client engagements\n\nSKILLS\nAWS (ECS, Lambda, RDS, VPC, IAM), Kubernetes, Docker, Terraform, GitHub Actions, GitLab CI, Python, Bash, Prometheus, Grafana, Semgrep, Snyk\n\nEDUCATION\nBSc Software Engineering \u2014 Queen Mary University of London (2017\u20132020)\n\nCERTIFICATIONS\nAWS Solutions Architect \u2013 Associate\n\nRIGHT TO WORK\nIrish/British dual citizen", "raw_linkedin": "DevOps engineer with a software background \u2014 which means I actually understand why developers hate slow CI builds. Four years into the infrastructure side after starting as a software engineer, and I've found my niche in the CI/CD and developer experience space. Currently at Farewill making sure code gets from laptop to production reliably and fast. Looking for a senior DevOps or platform engineering role where developer experience is taken seriously.", "raw_interview_transcript": "Interviewer: Liam, tell me about how you got build times from 18 to 6 minutes.\n\nLiam: When I joined, every CI job was starting from scratch \u2014 no layer caching, no dependency caching, sequential stages that could have been parallel. I did a systematic audit of the top 10 slowest pipelines. The biggest wins were: Docker layer caching with BuildKit (halved image build times on its own), caching node_modules and Python virtualenvs with GitHub Actions cache, and parallelising the test suite using matrix builds. The six-minute average is now across all services; some of the simpler ones are under two minutes.\n\nInterviewer: You mentioned security champion work. How do you think about security in CI/CD?\n\nLiam: Security scanning in CI is cheap compared to finding issues in production. I introduced Semgrep for static analysis and Snyk for dependency vulnerabilities. The key challenge is tuning the signal-to-noise ratio \u2014 if you have too many false positives, developers just start ignoring the alerts. I spent time with each team tuning the rulesets so that alerts are almost always actionable.\n\nInterviewer: Where do you want to grow from here?\n\nLiam: I want to get into full platform engineering \u2014 not just CI/CD but owning the developer platform holistically. Kubernetes is an area I want to go deeper on; I've worked with it as a client-side user but I want to be the one running the cluster.\n\nInterviewer: Salary?\n\nLiam: I'm at \u00a368,000. I'd be looking for \u00a375\u201382,000.", "years_experience": 4.0, "skills": ["AWS (ECS, Lambda, RDS, VPC, IAM)", "Kubernetes", "Docker", "Terraform", "GitHub Actions", "GitLab CI", "Python", "Bash", "Prometheus", "Grafana", "Semgrep", "Snyk", "CI/CD", "Infrastructure as Code", "Containerisation", "Cloud Infrastructure"], "industries": ["Technology", "Software Development", "DevOps", "Cloud Services", "Retail", "Logistics"], "seniority_level": "mid", "management_experience": false, "education_level": "bachelor", "career_trajectory": "ascending", "interview_score": 0.85, "culture_fit_score": 0.82, "constraints": [{"id": "e5a62cd3", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Current salary is \u00a368,000 (stated in interview)", "canonical_key": "salary_min", "value": 68000.0, "operator": "min", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.98, "currency": "GBP"}, {"id": "f1aed1a9", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Seeking minimum \u00a375,000 in new role", "canonical_key": "salary_min", "value": 75000.0, "operator": "min", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.95, "currency": "GBP"}, {"id": "f08a893d", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Targeting salary range up to \u00a382,000", "canonical_key": "salary_max", "value": 82000.0, "operator": "max", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.93, "currency": "GBP"}, {"id": "beb139ff", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "career", "description": "Wants to transition into full platform engineering role, moving beyond CI/CD", "canonical_key": null, "value": "platform engineering", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.92, "currency": null}, {"id": "00b3dbba", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "technical", "description": "Wants to deepen Kubernetes expertise; seeks role running cluster operations", "canonical_key": null, "value": "Kubernetes depth", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.9, "currency": null}, {"id": "8c372d9c", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "work_focus", "description": "Seeks role where developer experience is taken seriously", "canonical_key": null, "value": "developer experience", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.88, "currency": null}, {"id": "ab63b611", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "ro